narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: We spent the semester doing a lot of readings. By L3 we were able to read news articles in stories in Czech which was very cool.
Learned a lot about Czech language and culture
I gained much information about the basics of not only the czech language, but also the culture of czech
A great understanding of the Czech language.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Karen Von Kunes is a brilliant professor, she is the main strength of this course as Czech is a difficult language.
It was a great course that prepared us to read in Czech. It is a really hard language to learn and the Professor did a great job of explaining grammar and giving us materials to learn from.
Should incorporate more vocabulary for a better baseline of understanding
It was a very good class because of the constant opportunities for help KVK offered.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, professor Van Kunes is very knowledgable and extremely good at working with students. Lots learned about Czech culture and language
I would absolutely recommend this to another student.
Fantastic course. Kvk is probably the best professors at Yale. Genuinely cares about students and is an expert in her field.
